review_blob: On tap. Amber and very clear with nice white head. Not too strong citrus hops aromas with some resins and floral background. Light to medium body with little bit alcohol feeling with the first sip. Then very well balanced. Quite drinkable, very good IPA.

On tap. Yellow, little but cloudy with nice white head and not bad lacing. Medium aromas of citrus and herbs, could have been stronger. Medium body with very stron bitterness finish. Really a good one.

On tap. Light yellow with nice white head and pretty good lacing. Strong aromas of hops with some herbs behind. Those herbs come also in a taste which is first little sweet and then finished with right bitterness. Medium body, oily with very nice mouth feel. Very good, very drinkable.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: Bottle. Maybe an old one as aroma was little bit pine but dominated by old hops. Also not very pleasant earthy bitterness, similar to regular Czech pilsner. Still nice dark yellow to amber color, short white head and not bad lacing. If oby have a chance will try another bottle or on tap.

Bottle. Dark brown, very clear with small head and pretty nice lacing. Aromas of chocolate, rosted malts and coffee, could have been stronger... Medium body with pleasant oily mouth feel. In taste rosted malts and coffee with bitterness in finish. Some sweet, vanila in the background. Very drinkable for its 8%.

Draft @ hops&hominy.; Dark yellow to amber color with small and short white head and almost no lacing. Amazig and very strong aromas of pine and citrus. Medium body, very rich with strong bitterness. Little bit of alcohol in a first sip, generally very well balanced. Decent one.

Tap @hops&hominy.; Gold with white longlasting head and pretty good lacing. Strong citrus and hops aromas with some flowers in the background. Light to medium body, oily. Moderate bitterness with nice finish. Great session ipa.

Bottle. Orange / amber appearance with nice frothy white head and good lacing. Aromas of citrus and hops, could be stronger. Light to medium body with medium carbonation. At first bitterness quite strong, grapefruit, not very pleasant, then some sweetness in taste. Pretty good ipa.

Bottle. Jet black with small and short beige head, no lacing. Very light, disappointing, aromas of roasted malts, with lightly peaty note in the background. Taste far better, medium body, very smooth with pleasant mouth feel, chocolate, little bit coffee and roasted malts. Low carbonated. Despite poor aromas very good stout.

Bottle, one year old. Dark copper with nice long lasting white head and pretty good lacing. Aromas of malts, rather weak. Light to medium body, medium carbonated, in taste little sweet with bitterness coming just after. With first sips feeling of alcohol, then well hidden. Was expecting sth much more complex, will keep second bottle another 12 months.

Bottle. Perfect style appearance: dark yellow to gold, cloudy, long-lasting white head. Good aroma of bananas and cloves. Dry, refreshing with pleasant fluffy mouth feel, high carbonation. Very drinkable.

Bottle. Jet black with almost no head. Aromas of chocolate, roasted malts, lactose. Not very intensive. Medium body, smooth and pleasant mouth feel, after few sips starts to be spicy what is very interesting at the beginning but starts to be annoying at the end of the bottle. Not very drinkable, one bottle is nice to taste but... enough.

Bottle. Jet black with medium beige and quite short head but still nice lacing. Aromas more typical for stout, coffee, roasted malts, chocolate. Some notes of hops, but very light feeling of herbs or dark fruits. Light to medium body, very pleasant mouth feel, same roasted feeling in taste. Very drinkable. Not a typical bipa but a very good stuff.

Bottle (two in fact...). Amber, not very clear with medium but long lasting head and great lacing. Very strong flower and citrus aromas.Light to medium body, lightly sweet followed by heavy bitterness with long finish. Rough and strong. Made with no compromises so, not very drinkable but very good.

Bottle. Dark orange to amber appearance. Very nice frothy white head and perfect lacing. Very strong tropical aromas with some resin and malts hidden in the background. Quite high carbonated with medium body and pleasant mouth feel. Quite long bitterness finish. Do like it!

Bottle. Orange with frothy white head. Medium strong aromas of tropical fruits with a background of pine cone what gives a rough feeling. Do like it. Medium body with medium carbonation. Taste is bitter with some notes of orange, pine and little herbal, good bitterness. Good one!

Bottle. Orange, almost clear with nice white head. Intense hops aromas of mango, melon and other citrus fruits, but somehow broken with a kind of grass or resin flavour. Very nice result. Medium body, right bitterness and medium carbonation. Little bit different than typical ipa but a very good stuff.
On tap. Gold and clear with small white head, nice lacing. Surprisingly strong aromas of citrus, vere pleasant. Light body, medium carbonated, dry and very drinkable.

Bottle (2015). Jet black with small tan head, almost no lacing. Strong aromas of coffee and chocolate. Had another bottle ca. 12 months ago, remember well, the aroma was even stronger! Same in taste with some feeling of roasted malts, medium body with right carbonation. Little oily texture, good bitterness and taste staing in mouth for a long time. A good stuff.

On tap. Orange with not big white head and quite nice lacing. Nice and fresh aromas of citrus, strongest one grapefriut. Also fresh in taste, rather light body with light to medium bitterness. Not much carbonated, very drinkable, little bit below an "average IPA" but a good stuff.

Bottle. Jet black with nice medium tan head. Aromas of coffee, vanila, a little bit of chocolate, not very strong but very pleasant. Taste is coffee, chocolate, roasted malts, little sweet with bitterness in the finish, medium body, slightly oily. Well made stuff, enjoyed a lot.

Bottle. Jet black with nice frothy beige head but almost no lacing. Quite strong aromas of chocolate, coffee and some notes of vanilla just hidden behind. Coffee is first with taste, also roasted malts. Light to medium body, light sweet with bitterness finish. Very smooth and drinkable, alcohol well hidden. Good beer.

Bottle. Dark brown to black appearance with tan small head with rather good retention. Nice hoppy aromas of citrus with chocolate behind. Light body, very light bitterness. In taste some roasted malts with a little bit of coffee. Tasty and very drinkable.

Bottle. Amber with not very big head with good retention and small lacing. Strong aromas of citrus, melon and some herbs behind. Light to medium body, malty and hoppy flavor, right bitterness but with sth strange and little unpleasant in finish. Enjoyed.

Bottle. Dark brown with beige small head and some marks or lacing. Aromas of dark fruits and caramel, rather medium but very pleasant. Medium to heavy body, malty, roasted, caramel taste with right sweetness. Im not a big fan of bocks, this one was really good.

Bottle. Nice amber appearance with white frothy, but quickly disappearing, head. Almost no lacing. Strong aromas of citrus, grapefruit first, and mango with malty background. Really good impression. light to medium body with moderate bitterness (could be heavier), very drinkable. Just a well made IPA.

Bottle. Dark brown to black appearance with tan head. Very low carbonated. Aromas of chocolate, caramel and dried fruits. Full body with toasty, sweet taste and light bittersweet finish. Aromas could have been stronger but in general complex and very well made.

Bottle. Dark yellow appearance with nice white head and quite good lacing. Very strong aromas of citrus, well made. Rather light body with good bitterness. also citrus with some malts in taste. Very drinkable. Good IPA.

Bottle. Not much wheat in taste and in aroma. Dark yellow, cloudy, with small white head.Quite strong hopped, very nice aromas of citrus. Medium body, very fresh in taste and right bitterness. Well nade IPA.

Bottle. Almost jet black, with frothy beige head and pretty nice lacing. Aromas of chocolate, coffee with notes of cherry and whiskey just behind. Taste rather light, bitterness could be stronger, dominated by chocolate and roasted malts. Very drinkable!

Bottle. Jet black, nice frothy head with good retention and nice lacing. Strong aromas of chocolate, coffee, caramel with some hoppy notes hidden behind. Medium and short bitterness, medium body, very smooth with notes of roasted malts. Good stout.

Bottle. Dark brown to jet black with light beige head, good retention and pretty nice lacing. Strong aromas of citrus with some notes of chocolate in the background. Body light to medium, some bitterness with notes of roasted malts and chocolate. Well made and very drinkable.
beer_name: Jan Olbracht Rzemielniczy Piotrek z Bagien Black IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Jet black with nice almost brown head with good retention. Medium to full body, rather low carbonated. Intensive aroma of coffee, chocolate and caramel, with some malty notes. In taste coffee comes first, also some roasted malts, very smooth with little bit bitterness at the end. Very good and very drinkable.

Bottle.Gold to copper appearance with big head, quite nice lacing but short retention. Strong, really strong, aromas of tropical fruits with notes of malty sweetness. Medium body, short and very nice bitterness with sweet long finish. Alcohol is very well balanced, felt only in the first sip, then completely hidden, what can be very dangerous :-) Its more like double (triple?) IPA with some sweetness. Very good beer.

Bottle. Orange appearance with medium head, very nice lacing, good retention. Medium body with very nice smooth bitterness and some grapefruit tastes. Aroma medium to low, malty with some notes of herbs and citrus. Little bit disappointing at the beginning but, finally, a good beer.

Bottle. Gold with medium head and pretty nice lacing. Strong aromas of fruis and resins. Taste very fresh with rather light body and bitterness finish coming quite late after sip. Easy to drink, so can be dangerous :-)

On tap. Clear, brown with some notes of red apperance. Frothy and long lasting bedge head and nice lacing. Strong fruithy hopes aromas. Medium body with significant, maybe little too long, bitterness. Very well made black IPA.

On tap. Dark copper / brown appearance with small, but long lasting, head and nice lacing. Aroma, first, very dominating smoke, later dried fruits and honey. Taste little bit sweet, some warming alcohol in the finish. Full body, low to medium carbonated. Very well made.

Bottle. Cloudy light yellow with nice but short white head. Light sour, light body, light carbonated with taste of lemon, little bit fruity, no bitterness. Very refreshing and drinkable. Do not have wide experience with berliner weisse but this once seems to be very proper.

Bottle. Very dark brown appearance with nice, big, almost brown, but short head. Aroma of coffee, first, then chocolate, licorice and roasted malts. Very pleasant medium bitterness. Body rather light to medium, light watery mouth feel. Good porter, but knowing other BBNs stuff was expecting sth even better.

Bottle. Jet black with nice, solid, but short head. Aromas of roasted malts, coffee and chocolate. Full body, smooth and creamy, taste with little bitterness. Very well balanced. Not the first and not the last bottle :-)

Bottle. Dark brow with beige head, short lacing. Aromas of roasted malts with some notes of chocolate and hopes behind. Full, rich, creamy body with very nice bitterness finish. Very robust black IPA.

Tap. Very strong, amazing aroma of red wine and blackberry. Jet black with small, short, beige head, no lacing. Surprisingly light body, almost no CO2. Little bit sweet in taste with notes of wine, vanilla and, of course, bourbon. Finish with very light notes of alcohol.

Bottle. Very strong aroma of citrus, mango and, coming just after, honey. Copper appearance with small, long lasting head and nice lacing . Sweet in first taste with pleasant, short bitterness coming little bit later. Good stuff.
Bottle. Golden appearance with a fluffy white, long lasting head. Bananas and some citrus aromas with little bit cloves hidden behind. Very refreshing, quite light and very drinkable.
Bottle. Jet black with a nice, but small, dark beige head. Rusty chocolate aroma with some coffee behind. Little bit higher then medium body, nice bitterness. Very solid stout.

Bottle. Very nice, but not long lasting, dark beige head. Aroma of sweet malts, coffee and toffee, little bit roasty. Strong medium body with a short, light bitterness and sweet coffee finish. Well hidden alcohol. Very good option to celebrate International Stout Day 2015 ;-)

Bottle. Very nice and quite strong citrus aroma. Clear amber appearance with rather poor head and only small lacing (3 months till "best before" date). Pretty light in taste, definitively hoppy. Bitterness as expected, nice and short.
Bottle. Dark brown with vanishing light beige head. Quite strong chocolate aroma with notes of coffee.Taste a little bit thin, chocolate and coffee first, pretty high co2.

Keg. Strong, like a kick in the face, citrus aroma with some notes of grass and caramel (?). Very light and fresh in taste. Solid bitter finish. Copper appearance with white head and very nice lacing. Great session beer, could spend whole night with it.
